<div class="main-and-aside r">
    <div class="main" role="main">

    <div class="article-teaser">
        Londoners and visitors to the capital travelling by coach should plan their journeys carefully, as some services will be limited.
        
    </div>



 <div class="on-this-page">
<p>It is also essential to make advance bookings for all travel during this period.</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Christmas Eve</strong><br>Full range of coach services operating in the UK and to European destinations but services start to wind down after midday. Advance booking for travel on Christmas Eve is essential. 
</li><li><strong>Christmas Day<br></strong>Limited services to mainland Europe and express coach service to and from Stansted Airport. No services within the UK. 
</li><li><strong>Boxing Day</strong><br>Limited services operating to most destinations. Phone operator for details. 
</li><li><strong>28, 29, 30, 31 December 2005</strong><br>Limited services operating to most destinations. Phone operator for details. 
</li><li><strong>New Year's Eve</strong><br>Services operating through out the day - but advance booking essential. 
</li><li><strong>New Year's Day<br></strong>Reduced services operating. Phone operator for details.</li></ul>
<hr>

<p>For 24-hour information on public transport in London, please call: 020 7222 1234.<br><br>TfL's Realtime pages display live travel information on London's public transport network: <a href="http://www.tfl.gov.uk/realtime">www.tfl.gov.uk/realtime</a> </p>
<p>Journey Planner checks the transport network's status before providing results. The best available route is shown automatically: <a href="http://www.tfl.gov.uk/journeyplanner">www.tfl.gov.uk/journeyplanner</a> </p>
<p>Travel alerts via SMS and email can be set up at: <a href="http://www.tfl.gov.uk/alerts">www.tfl.gov.uk/alerts</a></p>

     

        
        
        
